# 7. Update `handleCallback()` in `AuthService`

After you create the Arthur session, create a handoff.

```java
public AuthResult handleCallback(String code, String state) {
    AuthTransaction tx = redisAuthTransactionService.findByState(state);
    if (tx == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Invalid or expired state");
    }

    AppConfigResponse appConfig = lancelotClient.getApp(tx.getAppId());

    // token exchange already working
    Map<String, Object> tokenResponse = exchangeToken(code, tx, appConfig);

    String idToken = (String) tokenResponse.get("id_token");
    JwtUserClaims claims = jwtService.extractClaims(idToken);

    String userId = claims.getPreferredUsername(); // current mapping
    UserResponse user = lancelotClient.getUserById(userId);

    UserSession session = new UserSession();
    session.setSessionId(UUID.randomUUID().toString());
    session.setAppId(tx.getAppId());
    session.setUserId(user.getUserId());
    session.setUsername(user.getUsername());
    session.setEmail(user.getUserInfo() != null && user.getUserInfo().getEmails() != null
            && !user.getUserInfo().getEmails().isEmpty()
            ? user.getUserInfo().getEmails().get(0)
            : null);
    session.setRoles(user.getRoles());
    session.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());

    redisSessionService.save(session);

    String handoffCode = UUID.randomUUID().toString();

    LoginHandoff handoff = new LoginHandoff();
    handoff.setCode(handoffCode);
    handoff.setSessionId(session.getSessionId());
    handoff.setAppId(tx.getAppId());
    handoff.setRedirectUrl(appConfig.getPostLoginRedirectUrl());
    handoff.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());
    handoff.setExpiresAt(Instant.now().plusSeconds(60));
    handoff.setUsed(false);

    redisLoginHandoffService.save(handoff);

    redisAuthTransactionService.delete(state);

    return new AuthResult(
            session.getSessionId(),
            appConfig.getPostLoginRedirectUrl(),
            handoffCode
    );
}
```

